      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Back Bay is the classic Boston tourist spot, known for its tree-lined streets, historic brownstones, and upscale boutiques, offering a charming, walkable vibe that feels very welcoming to visitors. In contrast, the North End and downtown areas are more lively and bustling, with a mix of modern offices, vibrant cafes, and a rich Italian heritage that makes them feel more dynamic and easy to navigate. If you want a quieter, more traditional feel, choose Back Bay; if you prefer a bustling, energetic atmosphere, head to the North End or downtown. Both areas are highly walkable, but the North End might feel more \"central\" for a tourist wanting to explore the city's heart.",
